      "side": 1,
      "message": "[warning] Line 86: channelTimeout here is the mux liveness deadline (the comment even says \"a silent mux closes\"), so hitting it tears down the *entire* multiplexed socket to that device, not just the stuck message channel. Any calls, sync, presence or file-transfer channels sharing that socket with the peer would be collaterally dropped. Please confirm this is acceptable — a message channel that never gets ACCEPT/DECLINE arguably should fail just that channel\u0027s request, not the whole connection. If per-channel cancellation is available in dhtnet, prefer it; otherwise this collateral teardown should be documented in the comment as an intentional trade-off.",
      "revId": "8c656b5194a9538eb7d8892b51ea552857307fb3",
      "serverId": "1e26b4c1-6b8c-47ff-9df7-501b633d3b5a"
