      "side": 1,
      "message": "[info] Line 86: Reusing dhtnet::SEND_BEACON_TIMEOUT as the channel-reply timeout couples two unrelated concepts: it is the DHT beacon liveness interval, not a channel-request deadline. A future retune of the beacon in dhtnet would silently change message-channel behavior. Note the sibling SIP path (jamiaccount.cpp:4216) sets an explicit, purpose-specific value (options.channelTimeout \u003d 3s). Prefer a dedicated named constant (e.g. static constexpr auto MESSAGE_CHANNEL_TIMEOUT \u003d ...;) so intent is explicit and independent of beacon tuning.",
